    *   **Focus on `q c` and `d`**: The most promising targets for interception would be the methods of the `H8.q` instance (obtained via `config.c.value` in a Frida hook) and any callbacks or methods associated with `CameraPreview.c` (e.g., `config.d.value.onScanResult(...)`) to intercept scanned QR code data. Manipulating `config.d.value` could allow injecting fake scan results.

